reviews.text: Seriously good Chinese Seafood restaurant. Locals highly recommended.

A very crowded local Chinese restaurant with a signatory dish...Alaska giant crab.  A must order dish, preferably steamed. Served with red vinegar, it tastes so good. Portion good for 2-3 persons.  Around hkd1000. Environment is noisy though.

A restaurant providing dim sum at a good price. Have been here for a few times. No advanced booking is available for table less than 7 or 8 persons. Have to walk in and queue. There were quite a variety of dim sum: the deep fried spring rolls, chicken feet in soy sauce, steamed vermicelli rolls, garlic squid were all very good. If u want desserts, they were all just at about $10-20. I like their coffee layered jelly.
Good food in general although not perfect, very reasonable price, yet the washrooms are dirty

Wow the Chinese restaurant in Hong Kong is definitely way better then the ones in the states. The flavors is not even compare to the Chinese restaurant in the states. They have classic Chinese dishes and all are packed with flavor. Staffs are friendly and attentive. Overall if your in this part of Hong Kong definitely check this restaurant out you won't be disappointed.

reviews.text: 點心🆗
人氣很盛的食肆！點心與菜式多選擇，質量好。
唔錯，好服務，食物夠味，附近戶点心，稍欠缺味，價貴，海港点心雞腳好入味，飯香，粥清味。
下午茶時、被夥記催趕多次、要我們埋單走人，因要執枱預備晚飯用… 無奈要走!!
對食物方面是可以的，但坐位可能有些擁擠所以有些吵嚷
